overall experience of OECD countries suggests that in practice, employer, employee and 
government co-financing is often required. The proposed scheme would provide the unemployed with 
allowances for job placement and retraining and early re-employment incentives. While suitable for 
Malaysia's immediate need to improve support for the temporarily unemployed, a more 
